Study Title: Weekly Paclitaxel With or Without Pazopanib in Platinum Resistant or Refractory Ovarian Cancer
Brief Summary: The purpose of this study is to evaluate the safety and activity of adding pazopanib to weekly chemotherapy with paclitaxel for patients with ovarian cancer that is resistant or refractory to treatment with platinum based therapy.
Primary Outcome Measures: progression free survival, 6 months from randomization
Secondary Outcome Measures: number of patients with objective response, at 2 months and 4 months after randomization|worst grade toxicity per patient, at end of each 28 day cycle of therapy|overall survival, one year from randomization
Study Design: Allocation: RANDOMIZED|Intervention Model: PARALLEL|Masking: NONE|Primary Purpose: TREATMENT
